<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-28T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-28T16:00:00-05:00" n="653" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/2209: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé at Damascus</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Farrell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-28T17:00:00-04:00">March
                                        28, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5. You are authorized to reply to Syrian Foreign Office (your
                                telegram no. 3 and your despatch no. 81 of February 24, 1944<note n="87" xml:id="d653fn87">Latter not printed.</note>) in the same
                                sense as the Department’s reply,<note n="88" xml:id="d653fn88">See
                                    note to the Egyptian Minister, March 28, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> text of which is being repeated
                                telegraphically to you through Cairo,<note n="89" xml:id="d653fn89">See footnote 85, above.</note> to the Egyptian Minister’s note
                                regarding immigration into Palestine.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>